Sentencas: With respect to intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), electrocatalytic activity of the cathodes dominates their output power.
Titulo: Impacts of A-site gadolinium doping on electrocatalytic performance of La0.33Ba0.62Gd0.05Co0.7Fe0.3O3-δ to realize promising cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein A-site gadolinium-doped La0.33Ba0.62Gd0.05Co0.7Fe0.3O3-delta (LBG0.05CF) perovskite is synthesized and systematically evaluated as the cathode for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Impacts of A-site gadolinium doping on electrocatalytic performance of La0.33Ba0.62Gd0.05Co0.7Fe0.3O3-δ to realize promising cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We demonstrate outstanding catalytic activity of LBG0.05CF toward oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Impacts of A-site gadolinium doping on electrocatalytic performance of La0.33Ba0.62Gd0.05Co0.7Fe0.3O3-δ to realize promising cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Benefiting from enhanced electrical conductivity, oxygen surface exchange and diffusion rates, the ORR activity of LBG0.05CF outperforms that of La0.33Ba0.67Co0.7Fe0.3O3-delta (LBCF), as evidenced by the lower polarization resistance (0.035 Omega cm(2)) at 700 degrees C. The Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CGO) electrolyte-supported fuel cell with the LBG0.05CF cathode delivers a peak power density (PPD) of 371 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, which surpasses the PPD (278 mW cm(-2)) for LBCF-based cell.
Titulo: Impacts of A-site gadolinium doping on electrocatalytic performance of La0.33Ba0.62Gd0.05Co0.7Fe0.3O3-δ to realize promising cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, LBG0.05CF exhibits an improved CO2 tolerance compared with pristine LBCF.
Titulo: Impacts of A-site gadolinium doping on electrocatalytic performance of La0.33Ba0.62Gd0.05Co0.7Fe0.3O3-δ to realize promising cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results highlight a promising strategy of A-site replacement of Ba by lanthanide for optimizing catalytic ORR activity of the perovskite materials.
Titulo: Impacts of A-site gadolinium doping on electrocatalytic performance of La0.33Ba0.62Gd0.05Co0.7Fe0.3O3-δ to realize promising cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
